mily: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><strong>Drive<\/strong>: From Crawford Bay Village, drive on Hwy 3A south 19.6km.\u00a0<\/span><br style=\"font-size: 16px;\" \/><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">From Creston, drive on Hwy 3A north 51.5km. Cross Akokli Creek at 41.2km.<br \/>\n<\/span>Turn east into Lockhart Creek PP parking lot 540m (1770&#8242;).<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Trail.<\/strong>\u00a0Start on the signed trail. In 15 and 30 minutes, pass through some large cedars. At 4km, pass a cabin. Walk as far as desired. Going all the way to the ridge at the east boundary of the park is 13 km and a 1442m climb, but is increasingly overgrown and full of deadfall the higher you hike.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A maintained trail that starts on Kootenay Lake with a TH on a highway is detracted by being totally in the trees. Used mostly by locals as a shoulder season half-day hike and by visitors to the park.\u00a0 Location: Lockhart &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/12\/15\/lockart-creek\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":true,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-8926","post","type-post"